mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_Name.name: mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_Name
mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_Name.description: For future use. The current design does not use this name attribute but instead references a LIM or CM slot by its profile index; we may in the future support referencing a LIM or CM slot by its name as well as by its physical address. This name attribute consists of a null-terminated ASCII string; is read-only; and defaults to the ASCII form of this LIM or CM slot physical address.

mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_PhysicalAddre.name: mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_PhysicalAddress_Shelf
mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_PhysicalAddre.description: The number of the shelf that the addressed physical device resides on.

mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_PhysicalAddre.name: mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_PhysicalAddress_Slot
mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_PhysicalAddre.description: The number of the slot that the addressed physical device resides on.

mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_PhysicalAddre.name: mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_PhysicalAddress_ItemNumber
mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_PhysicalAddre.description: A number that specifies an addressable entity within the context of shelf and slot.

mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_AtmParameters.name: mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_AtmParameters_IncomingPriority
mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_AtmParameters.description: Specifies the relative priority of ATM cells incoming from this LIM or CM slot. A slot's incoming-priority is used to select the appropriate outgoing queue that is associated with the outgoing port from the internal ATM cell processing engine. All ports on this slot and all ATM service categories share the same incoming-priority. An outgoing port (from the internal ATM cell processing engine) can have multiple queues associated with a given QoS. The incoming-priority is used to select which queue to use among all the queues associated with the given QoS.

mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_TrunkCacConfi.description: Enable or Disable CAC on this port. yes: CAC is enable on this port. no: CAC is disable on this port

mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_TrunkCacConfi.name: mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_TrunkCacConfig_PortNum
mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_TrunkCacConfi.description: Identifies this trunk port within the system. It is a read only field.

mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_TrunkCacConfi.name: mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_TrunkCacConfig_LineRate
mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_TrunkCacConfi.description: Line rate of the trunk port in Kbits/sec. The trunk port can have real-time (guaranteed) traffic bandwidth up to this limit. In case of over subscription, there is no guarantee.

mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_TrunkCacConfi.name: mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_TrunkCacConfig_OverSubscription
mibProfHighSpeedSlotStatic_TrunkCacConfi.description: Allowed to specify over subscription to the line rate to a factor of over-subscription/10. e.g Allowed BW = (over-subscription * line-rate) /10
